   {:e #blake3 "57e2484d23429c89f0a026f0a79c0af337b20a1dacf88b3f0f3c5e67111e1353" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: The core dogfood validation. A clean-context subagent interacts with braid on the Go CLI as a real user would, without knowledge of braid internals. Tests whether Session 044/045 improvements (multi-membership, frontier steering, E[delta-F(S)] scoring, concept-level OAR, entity_label) produce a functional CCE from cold start.\n\nAPPROACH: Launch ONE subagent with this protocol:\n1. cd /data/projects/ddis/ddis-cli\n2. Run braid status (verify fresh store with innate concepts)\n3. Make 10 observations about the Go CLI codebase:\n   - 3 well-explored (parser: YAML validation, storage: 30 SQLite tables, events: crystallize-materialize-project)\n   - 3 unexplored (witness: challenge-response verification, challenge: adversarial falsification, absorb: external feedback integration)\n   - 2 cross-cutting (error handling inconsistency across packages, testing gaps in safety-critical components)\n   - 2 architectural (dependency diamond coupling, materialize as load-bearing correctness boundary)\n   Each with genuine domain insight, 0.7-0.9 confidence.\n4. After EACH observation, capture the full observe output (concept assignment, frontier recommendation, entity links).\n5. Score each frontier recommendation: 2=immediately actionable, 1=reasonable, 0=unhelpful.\n6. Run braid harvest --commit.\n7. Run braid status --verbose. Capture concept distribution.\n8. Query concept counts: braid query '[:find ?name ?count :where [?c :concept/name ?name] [?c :concept/member-count ?count]]'\n9. Compute entropy and report all raw data.\n\nSUBAGENT DESIGN: The agent prompt must:\n- Provide the braid binary path (/data/projects/ddis/ddis-braid/target/release/braid)\n- Provide the Go CLI path (/data/projects/ddis/ddis-cli/)\n- NOT reveal CCE internals, innate concept names, or expected outcomes\n- NOT tell the agent what score to expect\n- Require the agent to record EVERY observation output verbatim\n- Require the agent to score frontier recommendations independently\n- Require the agent to compute entropy from raw concept counts\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) 10 observations made with diverse package targeting. (B) All observation outputs captured verbatim. (C) Each frontier recommendation scored 0-2. (D) Concept distribution queried and entropy computed. (E) All raw data returned to orchestrator.\n\nDEPENDS-ON: S045-DF1 (fresh store must exist before subagent runs)." :op :assert}
